com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage

Class AdobePhotoCatalog

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePhoto
      • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePhotoCatalog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable

    public class AdobePhotoCatalog
extends AdobePhoto
implements java.io.Externalizable
    AdobePhotoCatalog is the topmost container of assets in a user's assets library. Each catalog contains zero or more collections.

      • listCollectionsAfterName

        public void listCollectionsAfterName(java.lang.String name,
                                     int withLimit,
                                     boolean includeDeletedCollections,
                                     IAdobeGenericCompletionCallback<java.util.ArrayList<AdobePhotoCollection>> completionCallback,
                                     IAdobeGenericErrorCallback<com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> errorCallback)
        Lists the collections in the catalog on the Adobe Photo Service asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        name - start the list results after "name," or nil to start at the beginning of the list.
        withLimit - number of collections to return. Default value is 100, max is 500. Note that the response may contain more than 'limit' number of collections returned if the collections at the 'limit' boundary has the same name after.
        includeDeletedCollections - true to include deleted collections in the response.
        completionCallback - returns a list of all AdobePhotoCatalog objects for the logged in user when complete.
        errorCallback - optionally be notified of an error.
